timeline.bodyText:
You should write this using vanilla js.
this.querySelectorAll(".sort_element_site").forEach(val => {
const className = val.getAttribute("class");
if (!className.includes(sortInputValue)) {
val.classList.remove("collapse-icon", "fa", "fa-chevron-down");
});
You get the idea ...
I want to steadily remove the use of jquery if there's a suitable alternative in vanilla js. The less dependency on jquery, the better. Also, if you have to use jquery, you should not keep wrapping an Element in a jquery object as it's really inefficient. Just use the Element if you can :)
I also have one more concern here. Why do you need to remove these classes in the first place? Can you not avoid adding them, in the lit-html template from the render method for that component?

